service 09.desc: VIN Message Count in PID 02. Only for ISO 9141-2, ISO 14230-4 and SAE J1850.

service 09.formula: 17-char VIN, ASCII-encoded and left-padded with null chars (0x00) if needed to.

service 09.desc: Calibration ID message count for PID 04. Only for ISO 9141-2, ISO 14230-4 and SAE J1850.
service 09.formula: It will be a multiple of 4 (4 messages are needed for each ID).
Up to 16 ASCII chars. Data bytes not used will be reported as null bytes (0x00). Several CALID can be outputed (16 bytes each)

service 09.desc: Calibration verification numbers (CVN) message count for PID 06. Only for ISO 9141-2, ISO 14230-4 and SAE J1850.
service 09.formula: Raw data left-padded with null characters (0x00). Usually displayed as hex string.

service 09.desc: Calibration Verification Numbers (CVN) Several CVN can be output (4 bytes each) the number of CVN and CALID must match
service 09.formula: 8 if sixteen (16) values are required to be reported, 9 if eighteen (18) values are required to be reported, and 10 if twenty (20) values are required to be reported (one message reports two values, each one consisting in two bytes).

service 09.desc: In-use performance tracking message count for PID 08 and 0B. Only for ISO 9141-2, ISO 14230-4 and SAE J1850.
service 09.formula: 4 or 5 messages, each one containing 4 bytes (two values). See below
